@twocol{
@ {
Suppose @math|{ \text{(*)} = 1 }|. What can we say about this?
}

@ {
Suppose @math|{ \text{(*)} = 1 }|. Then we have a system of equations
@Math|{
\begin{cases}
ad + bc = 0 \\
ac - bd = 1
\end{cases}
}|
Given this system, we can also say @Math|{
\begin{cases}
-ad - bc = 0 \\
ac - bd = 1
\end{cases}
}|
Thus, by regrouping, @math{(a-bi)(c-di) = 1}. @math{\square}
}
}

